OL,5, A convicted murderer has admitted at   
OL,6, the UK's first public parole hearing   
OL,7, that he covered up his wife's death.   
OL,9,FRussell Causley, 79, murdered wife     
OL,10,FCarole Packman in Bournemouth in 1985  
OL,11,Fbut has always refused to reveal the   
OL,12,Fwhereabouts of her body.               
OL,14,FHe told the hearing that it was his    
OL,15,Fex-lover Patricia Causley, whose name  
OL,16,Fhe took, who carried out the killing.  
OL,18,FMs Causley was never tried over the    
OL,19,Fkilling. Under questioning, Causley    
OL,20,Fagreed that he was a "habitual liar".  
